Rugby World Cup Final Weekend to Boost NZ Economy by $63 Million

-- B y   C h r i s   B o u r k e
-- 
2011-10-21T01:00:00Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/rugby-world-cup-final-weekend-to-boost-nz-economy-by-63-million.html
New Zealand ’s economy is likely to
earn a $62.8 million windfall this weekend as local and French
fans descend on Auckland for the  Rugby World Cup  final,
according to a study commissioned by  Mastercard Inc. (MA)   As many as 50,000 international visitors are expected to be
in Auckland for the tournament’s last weekend as New Zealand’s
All Blacks prepare to play  France  at  Eden Park  on Sunday,
according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
